LEPTOSPIROSIS - NEW CALEDONIA: FLOODING, HEAVY RAINS
****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 2 Mar 2022 11:54 AM NCT
Source: Nouvelle-Calédonie la 1ère [in French, machine trans., edited]
https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/nouvellecaledonie/recrudescence-des-cas-de-leptospirose-en-ce-debut-d-annee-1244011.html


In New Caledonia, 63 cases of leptospirosis have already been identified since January [2022]. 55 patients had to be hospitalized, including 20 in intensive care. Rat disease [leptospirosis] occurs every year during the rainy season.

In case of fatigue, high fever, muscle, joint, and abdominal pain, consult a doctor as soon as possible. Last year [2021], 4 people died of leptospirosis. Since the beginning of the year [2022], 63 cases of contamination [infection] with this bacterium, called rat disease, have been identified, of which 87% [55 of 63 cases] have led to hospitalization.

New Caledonia is not spared by this serious, sometimes fatal disease. Last year [2021], [there were] 229 cases. "It is a disease that is found more frequently at the beginning of the year. This disease must be diagnosed early enough, so that it can be treated as quickly as possible," explains Stéphane Chabaud, leptospirosis nurse.

"The time between when we are exposed and when we develop clinical signs [the incubation period] varies, roughly, from one to 3 weeks. At the start of the disease, the signs can resemble other diseases, such as dengue and COVID-19. If we wait, jaundice may appear," adds Dr Anne Pfannstiel, prevention doctor at Dass-NC (Directorate of the health and social agency).

"We have a resurgence of cases, usually in the 1st half of the year. In 1999, we had 19 deaths due to leptospirosis," she continues. In 2 months in 2022, 63 cases have been recorded. "It's huge, with 22 children affected. 2/3 of the cases concern the North Province," specifies the doctor. The province of the Loyalty Islands is, on the contrary, spared. Since January [2022], the youngest patient reported is 6 years old and the oldest is 71 years old. The greatest caution is therefore recommended, especially since this disease can be avoided.

[Byline: Martine Nollet (Gédéon Richard)]

